Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling,
add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to
medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove
the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another
~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its
own steam).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @courgette{1} then
quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Trim the
@green beans{80%g} then chop into thirds. Chop the @hake fillet{2} into 2cm
chunks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw fish.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} over medium high heat.
Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring, until soft and turning brown,
~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @Sri Lankan curry powder{1%tsp} (add less if
you don't like too much heat) and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @water for the curry{50%ml} and @vegetable stock
powder{1%tsp}, stir together and bring to a simmer. Add the courgette and
green beans, stirring occasionally, and simmer over medium heat until just
tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the fish to the curry and gently stir through. Cover with a #lid{} (or some
#foil{}) and simmer until the fish is cooked and the vegetables are tender,
~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Divide the rice between plates and spoon over the fish curry. Enjoy!